.TH SDL_GetTextureProperties 3 "SDL 3.0.0" "SDL" "SDL3 FUNCTIONS"
.SH NAME
SDL_GetTextureProperties \- Get the properties associated with a texture\[char46]
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "SDL_PropertiesID SDL_GetTextureProperties(SDL_Texture *texture);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The following read-only properties are provided by SDL:

With the direct3d11 renderer:


\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]d3d11\[char46]texture" (pointer) - the ID3D11Texture2D associated
  with the texture

\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]d3d11\[char46]texture_u" (pointer) - the ID3D11Texture2D associated
  with the U plane of a YUV texture

\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]d3d11\[char46]texture_v" (pointer) - the ID3D11Texture2D associated
  with the V plane of a YUV texture

With the direct3d12 renderer:


\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]d3d12\[char46]texture" (pointer) - the ID3D12Resource associated
  with the texture

\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]d3d12\[char46]texture_u" (pointer) - the ID3D12Resource associated
  with the U plane of a YUV texture

\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]d3d12\[char46]texture_v" (pointer) - the ID3D12Resource associated
  with the V plane of a YUV texture

With the opengl renderer:


\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]opengl\[char46]texture" (number) - the GLuint texture associated
  with the texture

\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]opengl\[char46]texture_uv" (number) - the GLuint texture associated
  with the UV plane of an NV12 texture

\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]opengl\[char46]texture_u" (number) - the GLuint texture associated
  with the U plane of a YUV texture

\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]opengl\[char46]texture_v" (number) - the GLuint texture associated
  with the V plane of a YUV texture

\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]opengl\[char46]tex_w" (float) - the texture coordinate width of the
  texture (0\[char46]0 - 1\[char46]0)

\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]opengl\[char46]tex_h" (float) - the texture coordinate height of the
  texture (0\[char46]0 - 1\[char46]0)

With the opengles2 renderer:


\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]opengles2\[char46]texture" (number) - the GLuint texture associated
  with the texture

\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]opengles2\[char46]texture_uv" (number) - the GLuint texture
  associated with the UV plane of an NV12 texture

\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]opengles2\[char46]texture_u" (number) - the GLuint texture
  associated with the U plane of a YUV texture

\(bu "SDL\[char46]texture\[char46]opengles2\[char46]texture_v" (number) - the GLuint texture
  associated with the V plane of a YUV texture

.SH FUNCTION PARAMETERS
.TP
.I texture
the texture to query
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns a valid property ID on success or 0 on failure; call

.BR SDL_GetError
() for more information\[char46]

.SH AVAILABILITY
This function is available since SDL 3\[char46]0\[char46]0\[char46]

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR SDL_GetProperty (3),
